|url = http://www.charles-leclerc-fans.com/2013/09/13/exclu-jules-bianchi-nous-parle-de-charles-leclerc/|accessdate = 27 November 2015}}</ref> In an interview in 2018, Leclerc revealed that Bianchi was also his godfather.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UZfmoNOmwew|title=Charles Leclerc's Walk to Work \u2013 2018 Monaco Grand Prix|publisher=FORMULA 1|accessdate=25 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nLeclerc has an older brother, Lorenzo, and a younger brother, Arthur. His father, Herv\u00e9, also raced cars, driving in Formula 3 in the 1980s and 1990s, and was well respected in karting. He died after a long illness, aged 54, just four days before his son won the feature race at the [[2017 Baku FIA Formula 2 round|2017 Formula 2 Baku weekend]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cikfia.com/newsroom/view/article/herve-leclerc-passes-away.html|title=Herv\u00e9 Leclerc passes away : CIKFIA|last=CIKFIA|website=www.cikfia.com|language=en-EN|access-date=8 August 2017}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/130319|title=Charles Leclerc: Emotional Baku Formula 2 pole was for late father|last=Kalinauckas|first=Valentin Khorounzhiy and Alex|work=Autosport.com|access-date=8 August 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n\nHe was in a relationship with the Italian, Monaco-based university student Giada Gianni from January 2015 until September 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://celebritywshow.com/sport/who-is-charles-leclercs-girlfriend-giada-gianni-when-did-the-ferrari-f1-ace-start-dating-her-and-is-he-related-to-jules-bianchi/|title=Who is Charles Leclerc's girlfriend Giada Gianni, when did the Ferrari F1 ace start dating her and is he related to Jules Bianchi?|date=2019-03-17|website=CelebrityWShow|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-13}}</ref>\n\n{{As of|March 2020}}, he is in a relationship with Monaco-based model and Instagram influencer Charlotte Sin\u00e9.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.essentiallysports.com/f1-ferrari-who-is-charles-leclerc-new-girlfriend-charlotte-sine/ |title=Who is Charles Leclerc\u2019s New Girlfriend Charlotte Sin\u00e9? |website=www.essentiallysports.com |first=Dhruv|last=George |date=25 March 2020 |access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nBesides his native French, Leclerc also speaks Italian and English.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aXQFYsDFn1w|title=Intervista a Charles Leclerc|publisher=Motorsport.it Youtube Channel|date=17 February 2018|accessdate=1 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=N}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{official website|http://www.charles-leclerc.com/}}\n*{{DriverDB driver|charles-leclerc}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-sports}}\n{{Succession box | before = [[Antonio Fuoco]] | title = [[Formula Renault 2.0 Alps]]<br>Junior Champion | years = [[2014 Formula Renault 2.0 Alps Series|2014]] | after = [[Matevos Isaakyan]]}}\n{{Succession box| before = [[Esteban Ocon]] | title = [[FIA Formula 3 European Championship]]<br>Rookie Champion | years = [[2015 FIA Formula 3 European Championship|2015]] | after = [[Joel Eriksson (racing driver)|Joel Eriksson]]}}\n{{Succession box| before = [[Esteban Ocon]] | title = [[GP3 Series]]<br>Champion | years = [[2016 GP3 Series|2016]] | after = [[George Russell (racing driver)|George Russell]]}}\n{{Succession box| before = [[Pierre Gasly]]<br>(GP2 Series)| title = [[FIA Formula 2 Championship]]<br>Champion | years = [[2017 FIA Formula 2 Championship|2017]] | after = [[George Russell (racing driver)|George Russell]]}}}\n{{s-ach|aw}}\n{{Succession box| before = [[Kevin Hansen (racing driver)|Kevin Hansen]] | title = [[FIA Prize Giving Ceremony#Rookie of the Year|FIA Rookie of the Year]] | years = 2017\u20132018 | after = Incumbent}}\n{{Succession box| before = [[Pascal Wehrlein]] | title = [[Autosport Awards]]<br />Rookie of the Year | years = 2017\u20132018 | after = [[Alexander Albon]] }}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Formula One teams}}\n{{Sauber}}\n{{Scuderia Ferrari}}\